WEBVTT

0
00:00:23.556 --> 00:00:25.251
Wrong, as usual.

1
00:00:25.458 --> 00:00:28.552
The United States' lack of action
in Eastern Europe...

2
00:00:28.762 --> 00:00:33.165
...proves that the Soviet Union's aggression
at the Afghan border...

3
00:00:33.366 --> 00:00:36.494
...will not be opposed publicly
by the United States.

4
00:00:38.571 --> 00:00:43.873
lssue: The Soviet Union continued
its recent series of military exercises...

5
00:00:44.077 --> 00:00:47.274
...conducting a bomb test today
in the Bering Sea...

6
00:00:47.480 --> 00:00:51.416
...just 1,500 miles
off the southern coast of Alaska.

7
00:00:51.584 --> 00:00:55.987
President Richard Nixon
issued this warning to the Soviets:

8
00:00:56.122 --> 00:00:59.580
The United States does not start fights.

9
00:00:59.793 --> 00:01:03.422
Let it be clear we maintain our strength...

10
00:01:03.563 --> 00:01:06.361
...in order to maintain peace...

11
00:01:06.533 --> 00:01:10.264
...so any adversary
should ask themselves:

12
00:01:10.437 --> 00:01:13.531
"Do the consequences
of attacking America...

13
00:01:13.673 --> 00:01:16.335
...outweigh the potential benefits?"

14
00:01:16.476 --> 00:01:19.138
As a result of the Soviet activity...

15
00:01:19.279 --> 00:01:22.077
...the watchdog group
of nuclear scientists...

16
00:01:22.282 --> 00:01:27.686
...moved the Doomsday Clock
up to five minutes until midnight:

17
00:01:27.854 --> 00:01:32.154
destruction by nuclear war.

18
00:01:32.859 --> 00:01:34.554
Question:

19
00:01:34.861 --> 00:01:37.352
on a scale of <i>z</i>ero to ten,
<i>z</i>ero meaning impossibility...

20
00:01:37.564 --> 00:01:39.862
...ten meaning
complete metaphysical certitude...

21
00:01:40.066 --> 00:01:44.560
...what are the chances the Russians
will actually attack the United States?

22
00:01:44.704 --> 00:01:46.001
Pat Buchanan.

23
00:01:46.172 --> 00:01:47.503
Zero.

24
00:01:47.674 --> 00:01:50.302
The Soviets
would never risk going to war...

25
00:01:50.477 --> 00:01:54.311
...when we have a walking nuclear deterrent
on our side.

26
00:01:54.481 --> 00:01:56.972
You're referring, of course,
to Dr. Manhattan...

27
00:01:57.183 --> 00:02:01.142
...but does Dr. Manhattan's existence
guarantee world peace? Eleanor Clift.

28
00:02:01.354 --> 00:02:04.118
Well, it hasn't
stopped the Soviet Union...

29
00:02:04.257 --> 00:02:08.921
...from stockpiling record amounts
of nuclear weapons.

30
00:02:09.129 --> 00:02:10.824
You don't think it's just posturing?

31
00:02:10.964 --> 00:02:12.556
Maybe the reason
why the Soviets...

32
00:02:12.732 --> 00:02:15.257
...are doing these bomb tests...

33
00:02:15.435 --> 00:02:19.838
...is because they feel threatened
by Dr. Manhattan. of course.

34
00:02:20.373 --> 00:02:23.536
Maybe the whole world feels like that.

35
00:02:25.545 --> 00:02:27.979
Soviet ships have violated
the territorial waters-

36
00:03:04.817 --> 00:03:07.012
Just a matter of time, I suppose.

37
00:04:37.677 --> 00:04:41.340
lt's a joke. lt's all a joke.

38
00:04:41.981 --> 00:04:44.245
Mother, forgive me.

39
00:08:45.024 --> 00:08:47.993
l was a hero, goddamn it!

40
00:08:49.428 --> 00:08:53.558
...an act clearly meant to send
a signal to the government in Saigon...

41
00:08:53.733 --> 00:08:58.067
...that violence and oppression
is not the way to peace.

42
00:09:35.408 --> 00:09:37.899
Fuck you, pigs!

43
00:10:08.040 --> 00:10:11.168
Good luck, Mr. Gorsky.

44
00:10:57.123 --> 00:11:00.183
Get out of here, vigilantes!

45
00:11:07.833 --> 00:11:10.028
No!

46
00:11:36.996 --> 00:11:43.162
Edward Blake. Sixty-seven
years old. Six-two, a solid 225.

47
00:11:43.669 --> 00:11:45.500
Guy was built like a linebacker.

48
00:11:45.671 --> 00:11:47.571
Yeah, I saw the body.

49
00:11:47.773 --> 00:11:49.798
For a guy his age,
he was in terrific shape.

50
00:11:49.975 --> 00:11:52.671
You mean apart from being dead?

51
00:11:53.879 --> 00:11:55.369
That's plate glass.

52
00:11:55.581 --> 00:11:58.482
You'd have to step on the gas
just to put a crack in it.

53
00:11:58.684 --> 00:12:00.618
Had to have been thrown.

54
00:12:00.820 --> 00:12:02.014
Check the bedroom?

55
00:12:02.221 --> 00:12:05.122
Yeah. Drawers opened, tossed through.

56
00:12:05.324 --> 00:12:08.350
Mattress flipped. Probably robbery.

57
00:12:08.527 --> 00:12:10.017
or made to look like one.

58
00:12:10.162 --> 00:12:11.925
See this?

59
00:12:12.231 --> 00:12:15.462
- Shaking hands with the president.
Whoa.

60
00:12:15.634 --> 00:12:17.864
Think Blake was a spook?

61
00:12:18.037 --> 00:12:21.734
Government or black ops?

62
00:12:22.041 --> 00:12:23.941
l think...

63
00:12:24.243 --> 00:12:27.542
...this is way bigger than both of us.

64
00:12:30.649 --> 00:12:35.951
Rorschach's journal, October 12th, 1985.

65
00:12:36.155 --> 00:12:41.252
Dog carcass in alley this morning.
Tire tread on burst stomach.

66
00:12:41.494 --> 00:12:43.758
This city's afraid of me.

67
00:12:43.896 --> 00:12:47.855
l've seen its true face.
The streets are extended gutters...

68
00:12:48.501 --> 00:12:50.901
...and the gutters are full of blood.

69
00:12:51.070 --> 00:12:53.561
And when the drains finally scab over...

70
00:12:54.607 --> 00:12:56.871
...all the vermin will drown.

71
00:12:57.476 --> 00:12:59.876
The accumulated filth of all their sex
and murder...

72
00:13:00.079 --> 00:13:02.309
...will foam up around their waists...

73
00:13:02.448 --> 00:13:07.909
...and all the whores and politicians
will look up and shout, "Save us."

74
00:13:08.921 --> 00:13:12.550
And l'll whisper, "No."

75
00:13:14.059 --> 00:13:16.926
Now the whole world
stands on the brink...

76
00:13:17.129 --> 00:13:19.620
...staring down into bloody hell.

77
00:13:19.765 --> 00:13:23.326
All those liberals and intellectuals...

78
00:13:23.469 --> 00:13:25.460
...and smooth talkers...

79
00:13:25.638 --> 00:13:29.130
...and all of a sudden,
nobody can think of anything to say.

80
00:13:29.275 --> 00:13:32.438
Beneath me, this awful city.

81
00:13:32.645 --> 00:13:36.376
lt screams like an abattoir
full of retarded children...

82
00:13:36.582 --> 00:13:41.178
...and the night reeks of fornication
and bad consciences.

83
00:15:01.734 --> 00:15:05.898
Tonight, a comedian died in New York.

84
00:15:06.038 --> 00:15:07.403
Somebody knows why.

85
00:15:08.340 --> 00:15:10.604
Somebody knows.

86
00:15:11.343 --> 00:15:17.612
lt all started with the gangs.
You know, people tend to forget that.

87
00:15:18.317 --> 00:15:21.343
Pirate outfits, ghosts.

88
00:15:21.553 --> 00:15:24.113
They thought it was funny:
dress up and pull heists.

89
00:15:25.858 --> 00:15:28.554
As soon as we'd arrest them,
they'd be back on the street.

90
00:15:28.727 --> 00:15:32.561
Nobody could pick them out of a lineup
because of the damn masks.

91
00:15:32.731 --> 00:15:35.029
So a few of us cops, we get together...

92
00:15:35.167 --> 00:15:38.534
...and we figure, what the heck,
we'll mask up, too.

93
00:15:38.737 --> 00:15:41.433
We'll finish what the law couldn't.

94
00:15:42.241 --> 00:15:46.234
Pretty soon, the papers get wind of it.
They ran with it...

95
00:15:46.445 --> 00:15:50.074
...and Oh, boy, we're a national pastime.

96
00:15:50.282 --> 00:15:53.740
lt was me, Dollar Bill, Mothman...

97
00:15:53.953 --> 00:15:57.354
...Captain Metropolis, Hooded Justice...

98
00:15:57.489 --> 00:16:00.617
...Silk Spectre and the Comedian.

99
00:16:00.793 --> 00:16:04.320
Oh, don't get me started on him.

100
00:16:06.498 --> 00:16:10.525
l must be drunk already,
telling you this sob story again.

101
00:16:10.703 --> 00:16:12.603
l think you were trying to make a point.

102
00:16:13.505 --> 00:16:19.637
Well, my point is that we had it too easy.
lt wasn't fair what happened to you guys-

103
00:16:19.812 --> 00:16:23.942
You guys who picked up where we left off.
- with Nixon forcing you out.

104
00:16:25.017 --> 00:16:29.454
Nixon, Oh, that prick. To think I voted
for that prick five times.

105
00:16:29.655 --> 00:16:32.419
Hey, it was him or the commies, right?

106
00:16:35.227 --> 00:16:39.027
Oh, wow, it's almost midnight.
Gotta go.

107
00:16:40.532 --> 00:16:42.159
Truth?

108
00:16:42.835 --> 00:16:46.566
You were a better Nite owl
than I ever was, Danny boy.

109
00:16:46.739 --> 00:16:50.470
- Hollis, we both know that's bullshit.
- Hey.

110
00:16:50.642 --> 00:16:51.939
Watch it with the language.

111
00:16:52.077 --> 00:16:54.739
This is the left hook
that floored Captain Axis, remember?

112
00:16:54.880 --> 00:16:55.938
Yeah.

113
00:16:56.582 --> 00:16:58.641
Next week?
HoLLlS: Well...

114
00:16:58.851 --> 00:17:03.379
...you know, you don't have to
keep humoring me like this.

115
00:17:03.589 --> 00:17:05.716
lf you got a hot date or something...

116
00:17:05.891 --> 00:17:08.689
Hey, us retired guys
have to stick together, right?

117
00:17:10.496 --> 00:17:12.327
You ever miss it?

118
00:17:13.532 --> 00:17:15.625
No. You?

119
00:17:16.201 --> 00:17:17.998
Oh, heck, no.

120
00:17:19.304 --> 00:17:21.101
Be seeing you.

121
00:18:22.101 --> 00:18:23.398
Hello, Daniel.

122
00:18:24.103 --> 00:18:25.195
Rorschach.

123
00:18:26.305 --> 00:18:30.605
Helped myself to some beans.
Hope you don't mind.

124
00:18:30.742 --> 00:18:33.210
No, no. Course not.

125
00:18:34.813 --> 00:18:37.338
You want me to heat those up for you?

126
00:18:37.549 --> 00:18:39.039
Fine like this.

127
00:18:40.652 --> 00:18:41.812
How have you been keeping?

128
00:18:46.225 --> 00:18:48.022
Out of prison.

129
00:18:48.527 --> 00:18:50.017
So far.

130
00:18:50.963 --> 00:18:52.123
Daniel...

131
00:18:52.764 --> 00:18:54.254
...look at this.

132
00:19:01.473 --> 00:19:04.067
ls this bean juice?
RoRSCHACH: Human bean juice.

133
00:19:04.776 --> 00:19:09.270
Badge belonged to the Comedian.
Blood too. He's dead.

134
00:19:11.316 --> 00:19:12.783
Let's talk downstairs.

135
00:19:13.585 --> 00:19:15.314
lt could have been a burglary.

136
00:19:15.521 --> 00:19:18.217
Maybe the killer didn't know
who the Comedian was.

137
00:19:18.390 --> 00:19:23.123
An ordinary burglar?
Kill the Comedian? Ridiculous.

138
00:19:24.696 --> 00:19:28.132
l heard he'd been working
for the government since '77...

139
00:19:28.300 --> 00:19:31.497
...knocking over Marxist republics
in South America.

140
00:19:31.637 --> 00:19:34.606
Maybe it was a political killing
or something.

141
00:19:34.740 --> 00:19:36.002
Maybe.

142
00:19:36.208 --> 00:19:39.439
Maybe someone's picking off
costumed heroes.

143
00:19:39.611 --> 00:19:41.704
You don't think that's a little paranoid?

144
00:19:41.914 --> 00:19:44.439
That what they say about me now?

145
00:19:44.716 --> 00:19:45.944
Paranoid?

146
00:19:46.151 --> 00:19:49.018
Look, Comedian made
a lot of enemies over the years...

147
00:19:49.154 --> 00:19:50.621
...even among his friends.

148
00:19:50.822 --> 00:19:53.017
Speaking of friends, how's Hollis Mason?

149
00:19:53.859 --> 00:19:57.818
He wrote that book. Said some bad things
about the Comedian in it.

150
00:19:58.030 --> 00:20:02.057
l don't like what you're implying,
and I like being followed even less.

151
00:20:02.634 --> 00:20:07.071
Maybe I was keeping an eye on you,
in case someone's gunning for masks.

152
00:20:07.239 --> 00:20:11.938
- You were never that sentimental.
- Attack on one is attack on all of us.

153
00:20:12.344 --> 00:20:14.778
What do you suggest we do about it?

154
00:20:15.681 --> 00:20:16.841
Retribution.

155
00:20:18.283 --> 00:20:21.582
- Watchmen are over.
- Says Tricky Dick.

156
00:20:21.753 --> 00:20:23.550
Says me.

157
00:20:26.158 --> 00:20:27.750
Nobody knows who you are.

158
00:20:27.960 --> 00:20:30.895
You can give it up,
try and have a normal life.

159
00:20:31.063 --> 00:20:34.965
That what you have now?
A normal life?

160
00:20:35.968 --> 00:20:39.369
When you walk down the street
in a city dying of rabies...

161
00:20:39.504 --> 00:20:40.971
...past the human cockroaches...

162
00:20:41.173 --> 00:20:43.903
...talking about their heroin
and child pornography...

163
00:20:44.076 --> 00:20:45.600
...do you really feel normal?

164
00:20:46.778 --> 00:20:49.508
Least l'm not the one
still hiding behind a mask.

165
00:20:51.416 --> 00:20:52.678
No.

166
00:20:54.386 --> 00:20:56.479
You're hiding in plain sight.

167
00:20:57.889 --> 00:21:00.016
Be seeing you, Dan.

168
00:21:00.459 --> 00:21:02.927
A maintenance hatch
will let you out two blocks north.

169
00:21:03.128 --> 00:21:04.823
Yeah, I remember.

170
00:21:05.030 --> 00:21:09.057
Came here often,
when we were partners.

171
00:21:09.234 --> 00:21:11.134
Those were great times, huh,
Rorschach?

172
00:21:11.637 --> 00:21:14.868
- What happened?
- You quit.

173
00:21:42.167 --> 00:21:43.156
Mr. Veidt...

174
00:21:43.969 --> 00:21:46.096
...to date,
you're one of only two Watchmen...

175
00:21:46.271 --> 00:21:48.705
...ever to reveal their true identity
to the world...

176
00:21:48.874 --> 00:21:50.808
...the first being Hollis Mason.

177
00:21:50.976 --> 00:21:53.968
And you've certainly profited greatly
by it...

178
00:21:54.179 --> 00:21:59.412
...turning your superhero alter ego,
o<i>z</i>ymandias, into a billion-dollar industry:

179
00:21:59.618 --> 00:22:02.610
Toys, lunchboxes, genetic engineering.

180
00:22:02.821 --> 00:22:04.812
l understand there's a movie
in the works.

181
00:22:05.023 --> 00:22:09.221
- l'm not hearing a question, Mr. Roth.
RoTH: l'm sorry. Do you think-

182
00:22:09.428 --> 00:22:11.953
The Watchmen resent me
for prostituting their struggle?

183
00:22:12.130 --> 00:22:14.860
lt's a fair question.
Yes, it's crossed my mind...

184
00:22:15.033 --> 00:22:18.059
...some of my old colleagues
might see it that way...

185
00:22:18.236 --> 00:22:21.228
...just as you're clearly aware
that biased journalism...

186
00:22:21.440 --> 00:22:24.034
...sells more maga<i>z</i>ines.

187
00:22:24.543 --> 00:22:29.276
The merchandising arm of Veidt lndustries
is funding our work with Dr. Manhattan.

188
00:22:29.448 --> 00:22:32.440
We recently expanded our research facility
in Antarctica...

189
00:22:32.584 --> 00:22:35.781
...in the hope of developing cheap,
renewable sources of energy...

190
00:22:35.987 --> 00:22:38.956
...that we might eliminate
the world's reliance on fossil fuels.

191
00:22:39.157 --> 00:22:41.591
Now, it doesn't take
a political scientist...

192
00:22:41.760 --> 00:22:45.161
...to see that our Cold War
with the Russians isn't ideological...

193
00:22:45.364 --> 00:22:48.856
...it's based upon fear.
Fear of not having enough.

194
00:22:49.201 --> 00:22:52.898
But if we make resources infinite...

195
00:22:55.374 --> 00:22:57.467
...we make war obsolete.

196
00:22:58.276 --> 00:23:02.042
l would hope the other Watchmen
understand that...

197
00:23:03.248 --> 00:23:04.909
...wherever they may be.

198
00:23:07.052 --> 00:23:08.417
Thanks for your time.

199
00:23:14.659 --> 00:23:17.321
- You look good, Adrian.
- Dan.

200
00:23:17.529 --> 00:23:19.724
lt's been too long.

201
00:23:21.466 --> 00:23:25.527
So Rorschach thinks
someone's hunting the Watchmen, huh?

202
00:23:26.238 --> 00:23:28.069
You think it's possible?

203
00:23:28.240 --> 00:23:30.970
Statistically, one murder
doesn't equal a trend.

204
00:23:32.144 --> 00:23:34.078
Rorschach's a sociopath, Dan.

205
00:23:34.746 --> 00:23:38.079
And so was the Comedian.
He was practically a Na<i>z</i>i.

206
00:23:38.950 --> 00:23:40.941
You know that better than anyone.

207
00:23:41.153 --> 00:23:43.348
l'm not here because I miss him.

208
00:23:43.555 --> 00:23:44.852
lt's occurred to Rorschach...

209
00:23:45.056 --> 00:23:47.991
...that we're the only ones
who know each other's identities.

210
00:23:48.493 --> 00:23:50.586
Actually, the whole world knows yours.

211
00:23:51.363 --> 00:23:53.854
That's why l'm warning you first.

212
00:23:57.469 --> 00:23:59.460
Thank you, Dan...

213
00:24:01.006 --> 00:24:04.806
...but I fear there's something
much more real to worry about...

214
00:24:04.943 --> 00:24:07.537
...than Rorschach's mask killer.

215
00:24:09.047 --> 00:24:13.609
lf the Russians do launch their nukes,
can Jon really stop them?

216
00:24:13.819 --> 00:24:17.414
The Soviets have 51,000
warheads stockpiled.

217
00:24:17.622 --> 00:24:20.819
Even if Jon stops 99 percent of them...

218
00:24:20.959 --> 00:24:25.157
...the one percent that get through
could still kill every living thing on Earth.

219
00:24:27.933 --> 00:24:30.265
Even Dr. Manhattan
can't be everywhere at once.

220
00:24:44.549 --> 00:24:50.146
Rorschach's journal,
October 13th, 1985...

221
00:24:50.355 --> 00:24:52.687
...8:30 p. m.

222
00:24:53.391 --> 00:24:57.293
Meeting with Dreiberg
left bad taste in mouth.

223
00:24:57.496 --> 00:25:01.489
A flabby failure who sits
whimpering in his basement.

224
00:25:02.701 --> 00:25:05.636
Why are so few of us left active...

225
00:25:05.804 --> 00:25:10.707
...healthy and without
personality disorders?

226
00:25:10.842 --> 00:25:14.107
The first Nite Owl
runs an auto-repair shop.

227
00:25:14.246 --> 00:25:17.647
The first Silk Spectre
is a bloated, aging whore...

228
00:25:17.849 --> 00:25:20.716
...dying in a California rest resort.

229
00:25:20.919 --> 00:25:23.444
Dollar Bill got his cape stuck
in a revolving door...

230
00:25:23.655 --> 00:25:25.145
...where he got gunned down.

231
00:25:25.824 --> 00:25:28.224
Silhouette, murdered...

232
00:25:28.560 --> 00:25:31.529
...a victim of her own indecent lifestyle.

233
00:25:32.063 --> 00:25:35.055
Mothman's in an asylum in Maine.

234
00:25:39.070 --> 00:25:42.233
Only two names remain on my list.

235
00:25:42.374 --> 00:25:47.471
Both share private quarters
at Rockefeller Military Research Center.

236
00:25:47.646 --> 00:25:49.978
l shall go to them.

237
00:25:50.348 --> 00:25:55.786
l shall go tell the indestructible man
that someone plans to murder him.

238
00:26:03.495 --> 00:26:05.292
Good evening, Rorschach.

239
00:26:05.497 --> 00:26:08.989
Dr. Manhattan, you know why l'm here.

240
00:26:09.134 --> 00:26:10.601
Yes...

241
00:26:11.836 --> 00:26:13.804
...but you're going to leave disappointed.

242
00:26:14.005 --> 00:26:17.702
Rorschach. You shouldn't be here.
You're a wanted man.

243
00:26:17.909 --> 00:26:20.104
Nice to see you too, Silk Spectre.

244
00:26:20.245 --> 00:26:22.304
l have a real name l've been using.

245
00:26:22.514 --> 00:26:23.503
Try it.

246
00:26:23.715 --> 00:26:25.808
Whatever you say, Laurie.

247
00:26:26.017 --> 00:26:27.211
What are you doing here?

248
00:26:27.419 --> 00:26:29.717
The Comedian is dead.

249
00:26:29.921 --> 00:26:31.946
Rorschach wants me
to look into my future...

250
00:26:32.324 --> 00:26:34.815
...see if the killer is ever
publicly identified.

251
00:26:34.960 --> 00:26:38.054
Already warned Dreiberg.
Came to warn you too.

252
00:26:40.765 --> 00:26:43.131
Even if I wanted to help...

253
00:26:43.735 --> 00:26:47.637
...my future is blocked
by some kind of temporal interference.

254
00:26:48.039 --> 00:26:52.135
- I cannot see it clearly.
- lnterference? Caused by what?

255
00:26:52.277 --> 00:26:55.678
ln all likelihood, nuclear holocaust.

256
00:26:56.448 --> 00:27:00.475
lf the United States and Soviet Union
engage in all-out war...

257
00:27:00.685 --> 00:27:04.621
...the resulting blast wave would produce
a sudden burst of tachyons...

258
00:27:04.823 --> 00:27:09.783
...particles which travel backward
through what you perceive as time...

259
00:27:10.428 --> 00:27:13.795
...therefore obscuring my vision
of the present.

260
00:27:14.599 --> 00:27:15.998
l must return to my work.

261
00:27:16.134 --> 00:27:17.294
Wait a minute.

262
00:27:17.435 --> 00:27:19.926
What if that's why
someone wants us out of the way?

263
00:27:20.105 --> 00:27:22.335
So we can't do anything to stop it?

264
00:27:22.507 --> 00:27:24.338
Goodbye, Rorschach.

265
00:27:24.509 --> 00:27:26.807
Took a lot of effort
to get in here to see you.

266
00:27:26.945 --> 00:27:28.310
l'm not leaving-

267
00:27:29.547 --> 00:27:31.913
- till l've had my say.

268
00:27:39.424 --> 00:27:42.359
Seems like there's a lot of things
you don't tell me these days.

269
00:27:42.527 --> 00:27:45.223
l didn't wanna worry you prematurely.

270
00:27:45.730 --> 00:27:49.826
lf Adrian and I can solve the energy crisis,
war may be averted.

271
00:27:50.035 --> 00:27:52.060
But you always say time is simultaneous.

272
00:27:52.771 --> 00:27:55.638
lf that's true,
then how can you change the future?

273
00:27:55.840 --> 00:28:00.777
lf only you could perceive time as I do.

274
00:28:00.912 --> 00:28:02.174
Please let me show you.

275
00:28:08.186 --> 00:28:13.123
Magic. Dreams. That is what I had before.
l was a hero, goddamn it!

276
00:28:13.291 --> 00:28:16.385
lt's not my fault you got old.
What do you have to complain about?

277
00:28:16.528 --> 00:28:18.996
l'm putting food on the table
for you and your child.

278
00:28:19.130 --> 00:28:21.894
Call your friend Eddie.
Maybe he can give you a better life.

279
00:28:22.100 --> 00:28:26.230
- lt was a mistake. one time.
- Man tries to rape you-

280
00:28:26.538 --> 00:28:27.903
Stop!

281
00:28:28.707 --> 00:28:30.140
Your mind goes to dark places...

282
00:28:30.308 --> 00:28:32.640
...and you wonder
why I keep the worst from you.

283
00:28:36.614 --> 00:28:40.050
- Say hello to Dan for me.
- What?

284
00:28:41.820 --> 00:28:44.618
You wanna ask me
to go to dinner with you...

285
00:28:46.324 --> 00:28:48.519
...like we used to...

286
00:28:49.928 --> 00:28:51.054
...but you won't.

287
00:28:51.830 --> 00:28:54.128
You know I can't.

288
00:28:56.735 --> 00:28:59.033
So you'll call Dan...

289
00:28:59.437 --> 00:29:01.564
...which is only natural.

290
00:29:01.906 --> 00:29:04.500
You deserve the comfort of an old friend.

291
00:29:38.843 --> 00:29:40.401
Dan Dreiberg's table.

292
00:30:01.566 --> 00:30:05.332
Did you know that
he and H.J. were? I had no idea.

293
00:30:05.837 --> 00:30:08.931
You remember that cra<i>z</i>y guy?
What'd he call himself?

294
00:30:09.073 --> 00:30:10.563
Captain Carnage.

295
00:30:10.742 --> 00:30:13.939
Used to pretend he was a supervillain
just so he could get beat up?

296
00:30:14.145 --> 00:30:16.545
Yeah, he tried that on me once.
l just walked away.

297
00:30:16.681 --> 00:30:19.741
He starts following me down the street
in broad daylight...

298
00:30:19.951 --> 00:30:22.681
...yelling, "Punish me! Punish me!"

299
00:30:22.954 --> 00:30:25.445
l'm just saying, "No, get lost."

300
00:30:26.658 --> 00:30:29.092
God, whatever happened to him?

301
00:30:29.260 --> 00:30:31.455
Oh. Um...
He pulled that on Rorschach...

302
00:30:31.596 --> 00:30:33.996
...and Rorschach
dropped him down an elevator shaft.

303
00:30:40.471 --> 00:30:42.871
Oh, my God. That's not even funny.

304
00:30:43.575 --> 00:30:46.066
- lt's a little funny.
- Yep.

305
00:30:47.979 --> 00:30:49.970
WoMAN: l'm glad I ordered
the four-legged chicken.

306
00:30:50.114 --> 00:30:52.105
lt's really good to see you again.

307
00:30:53.384 --> 00:30:54.874
lt's great seeing you too.

308
00:30:55.687 --> 00:30:58.178
Why'd we do it, Dan? Dress up like that?

309
00:30:59.390 --> 00:31:02.621
- No one else would.
- Yeah, but do you remember my costume?

310
00:31:02.827 --> 00:31:05.921
All that tight latex?
l mean, it was awful.

311
00:31:06.064 --> 00:31:09.033
Uh... Yeah, yeah, awful.

312
00:31:09.234 --> 00:31:11.634
But didn't wanna disappoint Mother.

313
00:31:11.836 --> 00:31:15.829
Wanted her little girl to be just like her
and fight bad guys.

314
00:31:16.474 --> 00:31:20.069
l think the Keene Act was the best thing
that ever happened to us.

315
00:31:21.145 --> 00:31:23.545
Well, we'll live longer anyway.

316
00:31:26.851 --> 00:31:28.341
What?

317
00:31:29.354 --> 00:31:33.848
Jon thinks, unless he can do something
about it...

318
00:31:34.692 --> 00:31:36.751
...that there's gonna be nuclear war.

319
00:31:37.195 --> 00:31:38.685
Soon.

320
00:31:39.564 --> 00:31:42.897
But I don't know what to think.
l mean, it's all...

321
00:31:43.067 --> 00:31:46.161
...quantum mechanics
and parallel realities with him.

322
00:31:46.304 --> 00:31:49.068
l never even know
what universe he's actually seeing.

323
00:31:50.375 --> 00:31:53.503
He just keeps getting further away
from me.

324
00:31:54.212 --> 00:31:55.873
Everyone.

325
00:31:56.981 --> 00:31:59.677
l can't even tell
if he actually cares about me anymore...

326
00:31:59.884 --> 00:32:01.818
...or if he's just pretending.

327
00:32:02.520 --> 00:32:05.455
lf he's pretending, it means he cares.

328
00:32:10.228 --> 00:32:12.219
Hold on, l'll get the door.

329
00:32:13.531 --> 00:32:15.328
Thanks, Dan.

330
00:32:15.733 --> 00:32:17.724
- Got it?
- Yeah.

331
00:32:22.540 --> 00:32:23.768
l'm sorry.

332
00:32:23.942 --> 00:32:27.844
l invite you out to dinner to catch up
and have a few laughs...

333
00:32:28.246 --> 00:32:31.579
...but there don't seem to be many laughs
around these days.

334
00:32:31.783 --> 00:32:35.583
What do you expect?
The Comedian's dead.

335
00:34:07.211 --> 00:34:10.738
Laurie? ls that you?

336
00:34:13.518 --> 00:34:16.453
Thought you'd be used
to traveling that way by now.

337
00:34:17.121 --> 00:34:21.114
Well, l'm not.
l hate it when Jon teleports me.

338
00:34:21.325 --> 00:34:24.158
Well, it beats flying coach.

339
00:34:24.529 --> 00:34:26.520
Margarita?

340
00:34:26.764 --> 00:34:28.925
Mother, it's 2:00 in the afternoon.

341
00:34:33.771 --> 00:34:36.069
Remember that guy
that writes me letters?

342
00:34:36.441 --> 00:34:39.740
He sent me an item of memorabilia.
lt's a Tijuana bible.

343
00:34:39.911 --> 00:34:44.075
This little eight-page porno comic
they did in the '30s and '40s.

344
00:34:44.282 --> 00:34:48.275
- He sent you this?
- Sure. They're very valuable, like antiques.

345
00:34:49.153 --> 00:34:50.780
Mother, this is gross.

346
00:34:50.988 --> 00:34:53.252
l think it's kind of flattering.

347
00:34:53.424 --> 00:34:55.688
Why do you always call me Mother
when you're mad?

348
00:34:57.061 --> 00:35:01.088
l know why you're here.
l can still read, you know.

349
00:35:01.833 --> 00:35:04.097
l saw it in the paper.

350
00:35:04.735 --> 00:35:07.636
Eddie Blake's funeral is today.

351
00:35:09.440 --> 00:35:12.432
Finally got his punchline, I guess.

352
00:35:12.910 --> 00:35:15.743
- Poor Eddie.
- Poor Eddie? After what he did to you?

353
00:35:16.447 --> 00:35:18.005
Oh, Laurie, you're still young.

354
00:35:18.816 --> 00:35:20.716
You don't know.

355
00:35:20.885 --> 00:35:22.614
Things change.

356
00:35:23.521 --> 00:35:26.251
What happened happened 40 years ago.

357
00:35:26.424 --> 00:35:29.723
l'm 67 years old.

358
00:35:29.861 --> 00:35:34.059
Every day, the future
looks a little bit darker.

359
00:35:34.899 --> 00:35:37.060
But the past...

360
00:35:37.568 --> 00:35:40.560
...even the grimy parts of it...

361
00:35:41.139 --> 00:35:43.733
...keep on getting brighter.

362
00:35:49.247 --> 00:35:52.080
l've got spots in my eyes.

363
00:35:55.586 --> 00:35:58.248
Stop it, Eddie.

364
00:35:59.257 --> 00:36:02.522
- Thank you, Weegee.
- Thank you, Mr. owl.

365
00:36:03.728 --> 00:36:06.925
Tomorrow, 3:00, my studio.

366
00:36:07.098 --> 00:36:10.295
- Little place on 21st.
- Sounds good.

367
00:36:10.434 --> 00:36:15.030
Wow, a real photo session.
Wonder how my hair will look?

368
00:36:17.341 --> 00:36:20.538
Oh, go ahead. l'll be there in five.

369
00:36:37.061 --> 00:36:38.119
Eddie.

370
00:36:39.163 --> 00:36:43.224
What the hell are you doing here?
You knew I was changing.

371
00:36:43.434 --> 00:36:45.026
Sure I did.

372
00:36:46.637 --> 00:36:48.229
Come on, baby.

373
00:36:48.673 --> 00:36:50.664
l know what you need.

374
00:36:50.841 --> 00:36:54.937
You gotta have some kind of reason
for dressing in an outfit like this.

375
00:36:55.079 --> 00:36:57.377
l said no, Eddie.

376
00:36:58.049 --> 00:37:02.884
- No spelled Y-E-S.
- No spelled N-o.

377
00:37:03.087 --> 00:37:06.488
- All right?
- Come on, sweetheart.

378
00:37:10.428 --> 00:37:12.020
Eddie...

379
00:37:49.934 --> 00:37:52.630
You little bastard.

380
00:37:59.243 --> 00:38:00.210
This what you like?

381
00:38:00.378 --> 00:38:02.869
- This what makes you hot?
- What?

382
00:38:13.391 --> 00:38:16.588
Things are tough all over, cupcake.

383
00:38:16.794 --> 00:38:20.890
lt rains on the just and the unjust alike.

384
00:38:21.032 --> 00:38:24.900
The Comedian was a little bit of both.

385
00:38:26.337 --> 00:38:29.704
And he always thought
he'd get the last laugh.

386
00:38:30.241 --> 00:38:33.301
Thou knowest, Lord,
the secrets of our hearts.

387
00:38:33.911 --> 00:38:37.244
Shut not thy merciful ears
to our prayers...

388
00:38:37.415 --> 00:38:42.011
...but spare us, Lord most holy,
o God most mighty...

389
00:38:42.219 --> 00:38:45.245
...o holy and merciful savior.

390
00:38:45.956 --> 00:38:48.720
Thou most worthy judge eternal.

391
00:38:48.859 --> 00:38:52.226
Suffer us not at our last hour
for any-

392
00:39:49.820 --> 00:39:52.220
Fireworks. You gotta be kidding me.

393
00:39:52.423 --> 00:39:57.122
You know, you'd think this goddamn
country had had enough fireworks.

394
00:39:58.028 --> 00:40:00.622
You know, if we'd lost here in Vietnam...

395
00:40:00.831 --> 00:40:05.768
...l think it might have driven us cra<i>z</i>y.
You know, as a country.

396
00:40:06.537 --> 00:40:10.234
But we didn't, thanks to you.

397
00:40:12.243 --> 00:40:14.143
You sound bitter.

398
00:40:14.345 --> 00:40:15.972
Me? Bitter?

399
00:40:16.147 --> 00:40:19.241
Fuck, no. I think it's hilarious.

400
00:40:25.589 --> 00:40:27.454
Oh, Jesus Christ.

401
00:40:27.591 --> 00:40:30.583
- Mr. Eddie?
- Just what I fucking needed.

402
00:40:30.761 --> 00:40:35.858
The war is over now.
We must talk about this baby.

403
00:40:36.600 --> 00:40:40.161
There's nothing to talk about.
See, l'm leaving.

404
00:40:40.304 --> 00:40:41.669
l'm gonna forget about you...

405
00:40:41.806 --> 00:40:44.673
...and your horrible, sweaty,
little piece-of-shit country.

406
00:40:45.209 --> 00:40:46.369
Get the fuck out of here.

407
00:40:48.112 --> 00:40:49.977
- No.
- Get the fuck out of here.

408
00:40:50.181 --> 00:40:51.512
You will remember.

409
00:40:53.317 --> 00:40:56.013
You will remember me and my country...

410
00:40:56.921 --> 00:40:58.513
...forever!

411
00:41:01.125 --> 00:41:02.956
My face!

412
00:41:05.162 --> 00:41:06.322
Blake. Don't.

413
00:41:07.131 --> 00:41:08.428
Blake!

414
00:41:15.339 --> 00:41:17.830
She was pregnant...

415
00:41:19.076 --> 00:41:20.839
...and you gunned her down.

416
00:41:20.978 --> 00:41:22.240
That's right...

417
00:41:22.446 --> 00:41:24.346
...and you know what? You watched me.

418
00:41:24.548 --> 00:41:27.540
You could have turned the gun to steam,
the bullets to mercury...

419
00:41:27.751 --> 00:41:31.278
...the bottle into goddamn snowflakes,
but you didn't, did you?

420
00:41:33.257 --> 00:41:36.090
You really don't give a damn
about human beings.

421
00:41:37.261 --> 00:41:40.094
You're drifting out of touch, Doc.

422
00:41:41.665 --> 00:41:43.860
God help us all.

423
00:41:45.870 --> 00:41:47.167
Medic!

424
00:41:54.011 --> 00:41:57.174
Most holy and merciful savior.

425
00:41:58.115 --> 00:42:02.313
He cometh up and is cut down,
like a flower.

426
00:42:03.153 --> 00:42:07.351
ln the midst of life, we are in death.

427
00:42:09.660 --> 00:42:13.323
Welcome to the first meeting-
- This is bullshit.

428
00:42:13.464 --> 00:42:17.833
For a guy who calls himself the Comedian,
l can never tell when you're joking.

429
00:42:18.035 --> 00:42:21.436
Watchmen. That's the real joke.

430
00:42:21.572 --> 00:42:24.370
lt didn't work 15 years ago,
and it ain't gonna work now...

431
00:42:24.542 --> 00:42:26.669
...because you wanna play
cowboys and lndians.

432
00:42:26.844 --> 00:42:29.244
Maybe we should agree
on no drinking at meetings.

433
00:42:31.048 --> 00:42:34.745
Rorschach and I have made headway
on the gang problem by working together.

434
00:42:34.952 --> 00:42:39.286
A group this si<i>z</i>e seems like
a publicity stunt. l'm not in it for the ink.

435
00:42:39.456 --> 00:42:41.253
We can do so much more.

436
00:42:41.458 --> 00:42:43.653
We can save this world...

437
00:42:45.262 --> 00:42:48.390
- ... with the right leadership.
- Yeah.

438
00:42:50.768 --> 00:42:52.497
And that'd be you, right, o<i>zz</i>y?

439
00:42:52.670 --> 00:42:55.468
l mean, hell,
you're the smartest man on the planet.

440
00:42:55.606 --> 00:42:58.268
lt doesn't take a genius
to see the world has problems.

441
00:42:58.676 --> 00:43:02.237
But it takes a room of morons to think
they're small enough for you to handle.

442
00:43:03.213 --> 00:43:07.206
You know, mankind's been trying to kill
each other off since the beginning of time.

443
00:43:07.351 --> 00:43:12.220
Now we finally have the power
to finish the job.

444
00:43:12.423 --> 00:43:16.052
Ain't nothing gonna matter once
those nukes start flying. We'll all be dust.

445
00:43:19.229 --> 00:43:21.220
Then o<i>z</i>ymandias here...

446
00:43:22.232 --> 00:43:24.530
...will be the smartest man
on the cinder.

447
00:43:33.444 --> 00:43:35.469
For as much as it hath pleased...

448
00:43:35.746 --> 00:43:40.649
...almighty God to take onto himself
the soul of our dear departed brother...

449
00:43:42.052 --> 00:43:46.079
...let us therefore commit his body
to the ground.

450
00:43:46.290 --> 00:43:49.748
Earth to earth, ashes to ashes...

451
00:44:09.013 --> 00:44:15.248
Watchmen! Police!
Police to protect the people!

452
00:44:19.823 --> 00:44:23.850
Attention, citi<i>z</i>ens.
We are trying to maintain order.

453
00:44:24.028 --> 00:44:28.465
You must clear the streets
until the police strike is over.

454
00:44:28.632 --> 00:44:31.829
lf you could-
Please, there's no need for violence.

455
00:44:31.969 --> 00:44:35.063
Goddamn it. All right.
That's how you wanna do it?

456
00:44:46.850 --> 00:44:48.442
There's no need for violence.

457
00:44:48.652 --> 00:44:51.746
Fuck you. Fuck you!

458
00:44:58.062 --> 00:44:59.757
Oh, this is getting heavy.

459
00:45:23.620 --> 00:45:27.021
Goddamn, I love working
on American soil, Dan.

460
00:45:27.224 --> 00:45:29.624
Ain't had this much fun
since Woodward and Bernstein.

461
00:45:29.827 --> 00:45:31.419
How long can we keep this up?

462
00:45:31.628 --> 00:45:35.223
Congress is pushing through some new bill
that's gonna outlaw masks.

463
00:45:35.365 --> 00:45:36.627
our days are numbered.

464
00:45:36.834 --> 00:45:41.066
Until then, it's like you always say:
We're society's only protection.

465
00:45:41.238 --> 00:45:45.834
- From what?
- Are you kidding me? From themselves.

466
00:45:45.976 --> 00:45:48.171
- Son of a bitch.
No, Comedian, wait!

467
00:45:49.747 --> 00:45:51.647
Get your stinking hands off me.

468
00:45:53.851 --> 00:45:56.285
What the hell happened to us?

469
00:46:00.524 --> 00:46:02.890
What happened to the American dream?

470
00:46:03.694 --> 00:46:06.527
What happened to the American dream?

471
00:46:06.697 --> 00:46:08.824
lt came true!

472
00:46:08.999 --> 00:46:11.024
You're looking at it.

473
00:47:31.849 --> 00:47:33.339
Edgar William Jacobi.

474
00:47:33.517 --> 00:47:37.351
Also known as Edgar William Vaughn.
Also known as Moloch.

475
00:47:41.425 --> 00:47:43.655
What are you talking about?

476
00:47:44.628 --> 00:47:46.027
l'm a retired businessman-

477
00:47:48.332 --> 00:47:51.165
Lie again, Moloch, I break another finger.

478
00:47:51.335 --> 00:47:53.360
l did my time.

479
00:47:53.537 --> 00:47:56.335
l'm not Moloch anymore.

480
00:47:56.940 --> 00:48:01.309
- What do you want from me?
- Heard you attended Blake's funeral. Why?

481
00:48:01.478 --> 00:48:04.970
l just felt I should...

482
00:48:06.183 --> 00:48:09.084
...pay my respects to the Comedian.

483
00:48:11.521 --> 00:48:16.288
- How'd you know he was the Comedian?
- He broke in here. A week ago.

484
00:48:16.426 --> 00:48:18.792
He had his mask off.

485
00:48:19.229 --> 00:48:22.721
- He was drunk.
- Enemies. For decades.

486
00:48:22.900 --> 00:48:25.926
- Why should he visit you?
- I don't know.

487
00:48:26.103 --> 00:48:29.038
l woke up in my bedroom
and there he was.

488
00:48:29.206 --> 00:48:31.197
He was upset.

