01:27:33.014 --> 01:27:35.414
l knew the girl was here...

993
01:27:35.617 --> 01:27:39.109
...but when I searched the place,
l saw nothing.

994
01:27:40.021 --> 01:27:42.421
And then I found her.

995
01:28:34.042 --> 01:28:37.307
lt was dark when the murderer got back.

996
01:28:40.214 --> 01:28:42.512
As dark as it gets.

997
01:29:09.577 --> 01:29:14.412
Oh, God.
Who's out there? Who is it?

998
01:29:16.217 --> 01:29:17.377
Who is it?

999
01:29:28.096 --> 01:29:31.532
What? What the fuck?
Who the fuck are you?

1000
01:29:31.699 --> 01:29:36.193
What the fuck do you want?
You killed my dogs, man!

1001
01:29:41.209 --> 01:29:45.737
You think I had something to do
with that girl? I found that.

1002
01:29:45.913 --> 01:29:48.404
What evidence have you got?
That's nothing.

1003
01:29:56.324 --> 01:29:59.122
okay. I confess.

1004
01:30:00.328 --> 01:30:03.024
l kidnapped her. I killed her.

1005
01:30:03.831 --> 01:30:05.230
Arrest me.

1006
01:30:06.033 --> 01:30:07.728
What? Arrest me!

1007
01:30:09.337 --> 01:30:11.328
l did it! I said I did it!

1008
01:30:11.472 --> 01:30:12.939
Christ.

1009
01:30:13.074 --> 01:30:17.374
Look, l've got a problem, man.
Fucking take me in. I need help.

1010
01:30:18.179 --> 01:30:24.948
No, don't. Don't do that.
Take me in. Don't! No!

1011
01:30:29.891 --> 01:30:33.383
Men get arrested.

1012
01:30:34.862 --> 01:30:36.853
Dogs get put down.

1013
01:30:41.669 --> 01:30:43.864
Tremors of impact shook my arm.

1014
01:30:45.273 --> 01:30:47.571
Warm blood splashed my face.

1015
01:30:48.810 --> 01:30:52.906
Whatever was left of Walter Kovacs
died that night with that little girl.

1016
01:30:53.915 --> 01:30:56.179
From then on, there was only Rorschach.

1017
01:30:57.685 --> 01:31:00.415
See, doctor, God didn't kill that little girl.

1018
01:31:00.855 --> 01:31:05.019
Fate didn't butcher her
and destiny didn't feed her to those dogs.

1019
01:31:06.227 --> 01:31:09.663
lf God saw what any of us did that night,
he didn't seem to mind.

1020
01:31:11.566 --> 01:31:13.431
From then on, I knew:

1021
01:31:14.735 --> 01:31:17.067
God doesn't make the world this way.

1022
01:31:19.073 --> 01:31:20.563
We do.

1023
01:31:21.242 --> 01:31:22.436
Hey, Rorschach.

1024
01:31:24.045 --> 01:31:26.036
Hey, you're pretty famous, right?

1025
01:31:26.781 --> 01:31:28.874
Rorschach, I heard your mother
was a whore.

1026
01:31:29.050 --> 01:31:32.645
Hey, you know what?
l'm pretty famous too.

1027
01:31:32.787 --> 01:31:35.347
- Ain't that right? That's right.
That's right.

1028
01:31:36.991 --> 01:31:40.188
Maybe I can give you an autograph.
What you say, big boy?

1029
01:31:55.476 --> 01:31:59.003
None of you seem to understand.
l'm not locked in here with you.

1030
01:31:59.180 --> 01:32:01.205
All right, that's it!

1031
01:32:02.049 --> 01:32:04.517
You're locked in here with me.

1032
01:33:06.347 --> 01:33:07.405
Laurie!

1033
01:33:08.616 --> 01:33:09.947
Shit.

1034
01:33:10.952 --> 01:33:12.852
Hold on.
- Fuck.

1035
01:33:16.123 --> 01:33:17.613
l got it, I got it, I got it.

1036
01:33:22.330 --> 01:33:25.731
l'm so sorry. I was snooping
and must have hit the wrong button.

1037
01:33:25.933 --> 01:33:27.332
- Are you hurt?
- No, no.

1038
01:33:27.535 --> 01:33:30.629
- okay.
- l'm fine. I just feel so bad.

1039
01:33:30.771 --> 01:33:32.762
No, don't worry.

1040
01:33:32.940 --> 01:33:36.239
lt's happened before.
Comedian did it back in '77.

1041
01:33:37.345 --> 01:33:39.176
Archie survived that.

1042
01:33:39.647 --> 01:33:40.944
Archie?

1043
01:33:41.682 --> 01:33:45.140
oh. Well, uh, short for Archimedes...

1044
01:33:45.353 --> 01:33:46.843
...Merlin's pet owl.

1045
01:33:47.955 --> 01:33:49.650
Stupid nickname.

1046
01:33:50.691 --> 01:33:53.455
How did you ever afford
all this stuff, anyway?

1047
01:33:53.661 --> 01:33:59.156
Well, my dad was in corporate banking
and left me a lot of money when he died...

1048
01:33:59.900 --> 01:34:03.199
...which always surprised me.
l mean, he was...

1049
01:34:03.838 --> 01:34:06.500
l think he was disappointed
l went into crime fighting...

1050
01:34:06.641 --> 01:34:08.336
...instead of following him.

1051
01:34:09.110 --> 01:34:16.107
Guess I was just more interested in
birds and airplanes, mythology and...

1052
01:34:17.518 --> 01:34:20.214
Must be nice having a secret identity.

1053
01:34:20.855 --> 01:34:23.016
A secret place that nobody knows about.

1054
01:34:23.224 --> 01:34:28.218
You can just come down here and hang out
without anyone checking up on you.

1055
01:34:29.730 --> 01:34:32.062
Nobody watching you.

1056
01:34:35.436 --> 01:34:36.460
Wanna try those on?

1057
01:34:47.248 --> 01:34:48.943
There we go.

1058
01:34:52.086 --> 01:34:54.077
Wow, these rock.

1059
01:34:56.957 --> 01:34:59.255
They amplify the spectral range.

1060
01:34:59.460 --> 01:35:01.485
Thermal imaging.

1061
01:35:03.197 --> 01:35:05.131
They work even better in the dark.

1062
01:35:10.104 --> 01:35:11.833
You can see me, right?

1063
01:35:14.008 --> 01:35:16.704
l can see everything.

1064
01:35:19.413 --> 01:35:22.905
l remember, no matter how black it got...

1065
01:35:23.250 --> 01:35:27.414
...whenever I looked through those goggles,
everything was as clear as day.

1066
01:35:29.724 --> 01:35:32.022
This must be the way Jon sees the world.

1067
01:35:34.562 --> 01:35:37.429
We should probably head up.
Food's getting cold.

1068
01:35:37.631 --> 01:35:39.724
Put those away when you're done.

1069
01:35:48.442 --> 01:35:50.535
Soviets are
finding themselves bogged down...

1070
01:35:50.678 --> 01:35:52.441
...in bloody house-to-house fighting.

1071
01:35:52.580 --> 01:35:55.140
Casualties on both sides
are said to be in the hundreds.

1072
01:35:55.349 --> 01:35:58.375
Civilian deaths are also alarmingly high.

1073
01:35:58.552 --> 01:36:00.213
Dan.

1074
01:36:00.921 --> 01:36:02.684
Jon sees a lot of things...

1075
01:36:05.092 --> 01:36:07.390
...but he doesn't see me.

1076
01:36:14.535 --> 01:36:16.093
Well, uh...

1077
01:37:09.690 --> 01:37:10.987
Sorry.

1078
01:37:13.027 --> 01:37:14.324
Come here.

1079
01:37:20.301 --> 01:37:21.598
What's the matter?

1080
01:37:21.735 --> 01:37:24.203
- lf you could just move a little...
- okay.

1081
01:37:24.338 --> 01:37:25.396
Yeah. There you go.

1082
01:37:25.539 --> 01:37:27.700
Soviet ambassador to the U.N.
had no comment...

1083
01:37:27.908 --> 01:37:30.138
...when asked if Dr. Manhattan's
disappearance...

1084
01:37:30.311 --> 01:37:32.905
...has fueled Soviet aggression
in Afghanistan.

1085
01:37:33.113 --> 01:37:35.707
Dan, what's wrong?

1086
01:37:37.418 --> 01:37:38.510
Sorry, l...

1087
01:37:40.654 --> 01:37:42.918
Yeah, I just need a couple minutes.

1088
01:37:45.125 --> 01:37:47.116
Oh, hell.

1089
01:37:48.929 --> 01:37:51.261
lt's been a long time, Rorschach.

1090
01:37:51.932 --> 01:37:53.422
Big Figure.

1091
01:37:53.767 --> 01:37:55.632
Small world.

1092
01:37:56.937 --> 01:37:58.427
l like that.

1093
01:37:59.240 --> 01:38:01.572
But you know, it is a small world in here.

1094
01:38:01.976 --> 01:38:04.774
And l've been in it for,
how long now, Lloyd?

1095
01:38:04.912 --> 01:38:07.073
Almost 15 years, Mr. Figure.

1096
01:38:07.381 --> 01:38:08.712
That's right.

1097
01:38:09.717 --> 01:38:13.209
Fifteen years since you
and that owl fella put me away.

1098
01:38:16.223 --> 01:38:17.383
So...

1099
01:38:17.925 --> 01:38:22.692
...Rorschach, that guy you burned is dying.
Could go any minute.

1100
01:38:22.897 --> 01:38:28.096
You know, by my count, there are more
than 50 people in here that you put away.

1101
01:38:28.235 --> 01:38:32.604
l been talking to every one of them
and they're all dying to get a piece of you.

1102
01:38:32.740 --> 01:38:36.039
This place is gonna explode!

1103
01:38:37.611 --> 01:38:40.307
Then, you die by inches.

1104
01:38:41.215 --> 01:38:42.910
Tall order.

1105
01:38:43.117 --> 01:38:45.608
l'm gonna tear this guy a new hole.

1106
01:38:46.320 --> 01:38:49.312
Relax, Lawrence. Soon.

1107
01:38:50.124 --> 01:38:51.455
Come on.

1108
01:40:12.940 --> 01:40:14.237
Dan?

1109
01:40:21.081 --> 01:40:22.742
ls everything all right?

1110
01:40:25.085 --> 01:40:28.054
l'm tired of being afraid.

1111
01:40:29.089 --> 01:40:31.455
Afraid of war...

1112
01:40:32.292 --> 01:40:35.853
...afraid of the mask killer...

1113
01:40:37.464 --> 01:40:40.661
...and afraid of this goddamn suit...

1114
01:40:40.868 --> 01:40:42.802
...and how much I need it.

1115
01:40:43.670 --> 01:40:45.297
Me too.

1116
01:40:46.807 --> 01:40:48.104
So to hell with it.

1117
01:40:48.976 --> 01:40:50.307
Let's take Archie out.

1118
01:40:56.283 --> 01:40:57.375
You're serious.

1119
01:40:57.584 --> 01:41:00.075
l used to be a masked avenger too,
remember?

1120
01:41:00.254 --> 01:41:03.417
l'm used to going out at 3 in the morning
and doing something stupid.

1121
01:42:05.419 --> 01:42:07.250
Rapid burner. Be advised, all units.

1122
01:42:07.421 --> 01:42:10.015
Tenement fire at 5th and Grand.
Rapid burner.

1123
01:42:10.157 --> 01:42:11.522
Let's go.

1124
01:42:16.330 --> 01:42:18.662
l can see it.
All right, hold on.

1125
01:42:29.643 --> 01:42:30.940
Dan, there are kids in there.

1126
01:42:31.145 --> 01:42:33.272
Everyone, stay where you are
and remain calm.

1127
01:42:33.447 --> 01:42:35.642
We're gonna get you out of there.

1128
01:42:35.849 --> 01:42:37.976
The roof's starting to cave.
Get me in there.

1129
01:42:38.152 --> 01:42:39.642
l'm gonna get you close.

1130
01:43:38.378 --> 01:43:39.743
Let's go.

1131
01:43:39.947 --> 01:43:42.040
Watch your step.
All right.

1132
01:43:44.384 --> 01:43:45.442
We're all set.

1133
01:43:46.453 --> 01:43:48.148
ls that everyone?

1134
01:44:12.646 --> 01:44:14.944
Bye.
Bye!

1135
01:44:18.552 --> 01:44:20.110
l can't believe we did that.

1136
01:44:22.122 --> 01:44:24.556
- They'll lock us up with Rorschach.
- Who cares?

1137
01:44:24.758 --> 01:44:26.726
World War lll could start tomorrow.

1138
01:44:28.829 --> 01:44:30.160
Right?

1139
01:44:31.832 --> 01:44:33.163
Right.

1140
01:46:39.826 --> 01:46:41.726
Come back here!

1141
01:46:44.331 --> 01:46:46.026
He's dead, Rorschach.

1142
01:46:46.166 --> 01:46:50.364
While everyone's distracted, we thought
we'd bring you a housewarming gift.

1143
01:46:50.537 --> 01:46:52.732
Something from the machine shop.

1144
01:46:54.341 --> 01:46:55.933
Hey, boss, you notice?

1145
01:46:56.143 --> 01:46:59.135
None of that "small world,
tall order" crap.

1146
01:46:59.346 --> 01:47:02.474
He knows once we slice open his lock,
he's next on the block.

1147
01:47:02.916 --> 01:47:04.076
Fat chance.

1148
01:47:04.785 --> 01:47:05.877
You're dead, Rorschach!

1149
01:47:06.086 --> 01:47:09.715
We got a prison full of killers out here.
What do you got?

1150
01:47:12.692 --> 01:47:15.126
Your hands, my pleasure.

1151
01:47:17.130 --> 01:47:19.098
Can't reach the lock. Should I cut the bars?

1152
01:47:19.299 --> 01:47:22.598
This riot won't last.
I've been waiting 15 years for this.

1153
01:47:23.737 --> 01:47:27.104
l'm sorry, Lawrence, but you're in the way
of my revenge.

1154
01:47:30.811 --> 01:47:32.540
Nothing personal, big guy.

1155
01:47:34.014 --> 01:47:36.005
Boss! Wait!

1156
01:47:49.329 --> 01:47:51.126
Now you find out what the score is.

1157
01:47:51.531 --> 01:47:54.659
one-nothing. Come and get me.

1158
01:48:00.674 --> 01:48:02.301
Come on.

1159
01:48:02.476 --> 01:48:04.103
So l've been thinking.

1160
01:48:04.978 --> 01:48:09.176
l feel that we have an obligation
to our fraternity.

1161
01:48:09.983 --> 01:48:13.077
- I think we ought to spring Rorschach.
What?

1162
01:48:13.220 --> 01:48:14.983
Someone set him up.

1163
01:48:15.822 --> 01:48:19.417
And this whole cancer thing with Jon,
it just doesn't make sense.

1164
01:48:19.626 --> 01:48:21.594
You didn't get it.

1165
01:48:21.895 --> 01:48:24.295
Yeah, but breaking
into a maximum-security prison...

1166
01:48:24.498 --> 01:48:28.127
- ... is a little different than putting out a fire.
- Yeah, you're right.

1167
01:48:29.035 --> 01:48:30.900
lt'll be more fun.

1168
01:48:35.041 --> 01:48:38.033
Hurry, Lloyd. I wanna
smell this son of a bitch cooking.

1169
01:48:43.316 --> 01:48:45.045
Yes.

1170
01:48:49.823 --> 01:48:50.812
No.

1171
01:49:04.704 --> 01:49:09.573
Never disposed of sewage
with a toilet before. obvious, really.

1172
01:49:10.377 --> 01:49:13.676
Two-nothing. Your move.

1173
01:49:16.683 --> 01:49:17.775
Get out of the way!

1174
01:49:51.451 --> 01:49:53.009
No. No.

1175
01:49:53.653 --> 01:49:55.052
Where's my face?

1176
01:49:57.624 --> 01:49:59.319
Don't kill me.

1177
01:50:03.029 --> 01:50:04.428
Your turn, doctor.

1178
01:50:04.564 --> 01:50:07.761
Tell me, what do you see?

1179
01:51:33.953 --> 01:51:35.682
Don't move!

1180
01:51:43.963 --> 01:51:45.760
Rorschach.

1181
01:51:46.266 --> 01:51:49.064
Daniel. Miss Jupiter.

1182
01:51:49.202 --> 01:51:52.603
Excuse me. Have to visit men's room.

1183
01:51:53.173 --> 01:51:55.107
Oh, for chrissake.

1184
01:52:55.969 --> 01:52:58.062
Are you all right?

1185
01:52:59.506 --> 01:53:01.633
Yeah. Just...

1186
01:53:02.108 --> 01:53:03.336
...heavy, you know?

1187
01:53:04.144 --> 01:53:06.237
War, jailbreak.

1188
01:53:06.813 --> 01:53:11.716
Don't worry about it. okay?
Everything's gonna be fine.

1189
01:53:16.723 --> 01:53:19.715
- Hello, Laurie.
- Jon.

1190
01:53:19.926 --> 01:53:23.521
- TV said you were on Mars.
- I am on Mars.

1191
01:53:24.130 --> 01:53:26.530
You and I are about
to have a conversation there.

1192
01:53:26.666 --> 01:53:28.133
What are you talking about?

1193
01:53:28.334 --> 01:53:30.962
You're going to try to convince me
to save the world.

1194
01:53:36.876 --> 01:53:39.868
- Laurie, don't.
- Dan, trust me.

1195
01:53:40.046 --> 01:53:41.741
l have to go.

1196
01:53:47.453 --> 01:53:49.387
Beautiful, isn't it?

1197
01:53:54.260 --> 01:53:57.195
Forgive me. These things sometimes
slip my mind.

1198
01:53:58.598 --> 01:54:00.395
lt won't happen again.

1199
01:54:02.035 --> 01:54:04.026
That's comforting.

1200
01:54:06.406 --> 01:54:08.033
Oh, my God.

1201
01:54:08.708 --> 01:54:10.539
l'm on Mars.

1202
01:54:12.045 --> 01:54:16.414
We need to hit up
underworld contacts, squee<i>z</i>e people.

1203
01:54:16.616 --> 01:54:19.312
Sure, why don't we just pick names
out of a phone book?

1204
01:54:19.519 --> 01:54:21.612
You forgot how we do things, Daniel.

1205
01:54:21.821 --> 01:54:26.258
You've gone too soft. Too trusting.
Especially with women.

1206
01:54:26.426 --> 01:54:28.519
okay, no. Listen, l've had it with that.

1207
01:54:28.728 --> 01:54:30.719
God, who do you
think you are, Rorschach?

1208
01:54:30.930 --> 01:54:33.023
You live off people
while insulting them...

1209
01:54:33.166 --> 01:54:36.966
...and no one complains because they think
you're a goddamn lunatic.

1210
01:54:48.982 --> 01:54:50.779
l'm sorry.

1211
01:54:53.486 --> 01:54:55.647
l shouldn't have said that, man.

1212
01:54:57.657 --> 01:54:58.988
Daniel...

1213
01:55:00.426 --> 01:55:02.894
...you are a good friend.

1214
01:55:05.798 --> 01:55:08.926
l know it can be difficult
with me sometimes.

1215
01:55:15.441 --> 01:55:16.931
Forget it.

1216
01:55:18.111 --> 01:55:19.806
lt's okay, man.

1217
01:55:21.047 --> 01:55:22.639
Let's do it your way.

1218
01:55:41.734 --> 01:55:43.031
Oh, God.

1219
01:55:43.236 --> 01:55:47.570
Pyramid Transnational.
Anyone heard of it?

1220
01:55:55.081 --> 01:55:56.548
Oh, you bastards.

1221
01:55:56.749 --> 01:55:59.843
l buy everyone a round
and you sell me out like this?

1222
01:56:00.987 --> 01:56:04.286
Back off, or l'll stick this glass
in your squidgy face.

1223
01:56:05.992 --> 01:56:08.927
Everybody stay calm.
We'll try to keep this brief.

1224
01:56:09.095 --> 01:56:11.393
Roy Chess. on Pyramid payroll.

1225
01:56:11.597 --> 01:56:16.091
Tried to kill Adrian Veidt. Dead now.
Did you know him?

1226
01:56:16.235 --> 01:56:17.930
No.

1227
01:56:19.305 --> 01:56:20.533
Yeah, yeah!

1228
01:56:20.707 --> 01:56:23.642
- I hired him. I knew him from the inside.
- You're a felon.

1229
01:56:23.810 --> 01:56:26.802
l was. l've been straight
ever since I got out, I swear.

1230
01:56:26.946 --> 01:56:30.712
l barely knew Chess that well,
but I was told to hire from the old life.

1231
01:56:30.917 --> 01:56:34.444
- Told by whom?
- My contact, Miss Slater.

1232
01:56:34.654 --> 01:56:37.248
Janey Slater works for Pyramid too?

1233
01:56:37.423 --> 01:56:41.416
Yeah, she was real nice. She said hiring
ex-cons was part of the company program.

1234
01:56:41.561 --> 01:56:45.258
Give people a second chance.
God, please let go! l'm telling the truth!

1235
01:56:49.435 --> 01:56:52.632
Janey Slater, Manhattan's old girlfriend.

1236
01:56:52.839 --> 01:56:55.535
Adrian might help us
find out who's underwriting Pyramid.

1237
01:56:55.675 --> 01:56:57.142
Follow the money.

1238
01:56:59.579 --> 01:57:02.673
This is where we hold our conversation.

1239
01:57:03.483 --> 01:57:08.477
ln it, you ask me
to stop the imminent nuclear war.

1240
01:57:09.088 --> 01:57:11.716
But why would I save a world...

1241
01:57:11.891 --> 01:57:14.189
...l no longer have any stake in?

1242
01:57:16.295 --> 01:57:18.320
Then do it for me.

1243
01:57:19.198 --> 01:57:20.597
lf you really care.

1244
01:57:20.800 --> 01:57:24.201
When you left me, I left Earth.

1245
01:57:24.404 --> 01:57:27.305
Does that not show you that I care?

1246
01:57:30.510 --> 01:57:33.411
My red world here, now...

1247
01:57:34.447 --> 01:57:37.348
...means more to me than your blue one.

1248
01:57:38.117 --> 01:57:39.812
Let me show you.

1249
01:57:57.970 --> 01:58:00.871
Bombers are fueled and ready, sir.

1250
01:58:10.216 --> 01:58:12.411
lt's time, gentlemen.

1251
01:58:14.587 --> 01:58:16.987
Take us to DEFCoN one.

1252
01:58:22.328 --> 01:58:25.422
Not in penthouse. Not in office.

1253
01:58:25.598 --> 01:58:28.499
What nocturnal proclivities
entice a man with everything...

1254
01:58:28.701 --> 01:58:30.430
...out into the night at this hour?

1255
01:58:30.603 --> 01:58:32.400
l'm gonna look for Adrian's itinerary.

1256
01:58:32.538 --> 01:58:35.302
Maybe he keeps on file.

1257
01:58:40.012 --> 01:58:42.446
- Something's not right.
- Agreed.

1258
01:58:42.648 --> 01:58:47.415
Janey Slater, Moloch, Roy Chess
all work for Pyramid.

1259
01:58:47.620 --> 01:58:52.216
Moloch said the Comedian mentioned list
with his and Slater's name on it.

1260
01:58:52.425 --> 01:58:55.724
Whoever owns Pyramid
could be giving these people cancer.

1261
01:58:55.862 --> 01:58:58.330
Setting Manhattan up.

1262
01:59:12.411 --> 01:59:13.571
Funny.

1263
01:59:13.779 --> 01:59:17.271
Ancient pharaohs looked forward
to the end of the world.

1264
01:59:17.483 --> 01:59:22.477
Believed cadavers would rise,
reclaim hearts from golden jars.

1265
01:59:23.122 --> 01:59:25.784
Must currently be holding breath
in anticipation.

1266
01:59:25.925 --> 01:59:27.187
Pharaohs?

1267
01:59:34.033 --> 01:59:36.092
Got a psych profile on Manhattan.

1268
01:59:36.702 --> 01:59:39.193
See what the corporate head-peepers say.

1269
01:59:41.207 --> 01:59:43.732
"Subject continues
to retreat emotionally.

1270
01:59:46.045 --> 01:59:49.105
lf the only remaining ties
were to be severed...

1271
01:59:49.749 --> 01:59:53.708
...we predict total detachment
from the human condition."

1272
01:59:57.823 --> 01:59:59.620
l'm in.

1273
02:00:28.487 --> 02:00:29.852
No.

1274
02:00:31.991 --> 02:00:37.759
Congratulations, Mr. Veidt.
Dr. Manhattan's energy reactor is online.

1275
02:00:37.964 --> 02:00:41.798
Your support and your enthusiasm...

1276
02:00:41.968 --> 02:00:44.266
...is what has led to this triumph.

1277
02:00:44.470 --> 02:00:48.463
on behalf of the research team,
we salute you.

1278
02:00:48.674 --> 02:00:51.074
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

1279
02:00:51.877 --> 02:00:55.973
What in life
does not deserve celebrating?

1280
02:00:56.983 --> 02:01:00.942
This is the new Karnak.

1281
02:01:01.153 --> 02:01:04.748
This represents the culmination of a dream
more than 2000 years old...

1282
02:01:04.924 --> 02:01:11.227
...a dream now assured
because of your unquestioning assistance.

1283
02:01:13.332 --> 02:01:15.027
And for this...

1284
02:01:15.835 --> 02:01:18.167
...l am ashamed...

1285
02:01:19.338 --> 02:01:23.672
...ashamed that you must now share
such inadequate a reward.

1286
02:01:25.344 --> 02:01:27.335
To the pharaohs...

1287
02:01:28.281 --> 02:01:31.273
...their greatest secrets
entrusted to their servants...

1288
02:01:31.951 --> 02:01:36.285
...buried alive with them
in sand-floored chambers.

1289
02:01:37.156 --> 02:01:39.556
Sleep well, gentlemen.

1290
02:01:40.259 --> 02:01:43.558
our new, peaceful world
will be indebted...

1291
02:01:43.896 --> 02:01:46.456
...to your great sacrifice.

1292
02:01:47.400 --> 02:01:49.595
Bubastis.

1293
02:01:53.773 --> 02:01:56.765
Rorschach's journal. Final entry.

1294
02:01:57.109 --> 02:01:59.600
Veidt's behind everything.

1295
02:01:59.779 --> 02:02:01.303
Why?

1296
02:02:01.514 --> 02:02:03.539
What's his endgame?

1297
02:02:03.749 --> 02:02:07.412
l cannot imagine
a more dangerous opponent.

1298
02:02:07.620 --> 02:02:11.056
Used to joke he was fast enough
to catch a bullet.

1299
02:02:11.223 --> 02:02:14.124
He could kill us both alone in the snow.

1300
02:02:14.327 --> 02:02:18.024
That's where we're going now:
Antarctica.

1301
02:02:18.164 --> 02:02:20.928
Whether l'm alive or dead
upon this reading...

1302
02:02:21.133 --> 02:02:25.365
...l hope the world survives long enough
for this journal to reach you.

1303
02:02:25.538 --> 02:02:28.132
l live my life free of compromise...

1304
02:02:28.274 --> 02:02:32.233
...and step into the shadow
without complaint or regret.

1305
02:02:32.845 --> 02:02:35.837
Rorschach, November 1st.

1306
02:02:36.048 --> 02:02:39.540
Can't you just tell me how
this ends and save us the trouble?

1307
02:02:40.553 --> 02:02:42.453
lt ends with you in tears.

1308
02:02:42.655 --> 02:02:46.250
Tears? So you don't come back to Earth.

1309
02:02:46.392 --> 02:02:49.850
At some point, yes.

1310
02:02:50.896 --> 02:02:53.865
The streets are filled with death.

1311
02:02:53.999 --> 02:02:56.058
Jon, please.

1312
02:02:56.268 --> 02:03:00.728
You have to stop this. Everyone will die.

1313
02:03:00.906 --> 02:03:05.240
And the universe will not even notice.

1314
02:03:07.713 --> 02:03:11.911
ln my opinion, the existence of life...

1315
02:03:12.818 --> 02:03:15.810
...is a highly overrated phenomenon.

1316
02:03:17.723 --> 02:03:20.021
Just look around you.

1317
02:03:22.762 --> 02:03:27.131
Mars gets along perfectly well
without so much as a microorganism.

1318
02:03:27.733 --> 02:03:32.329
Here, it's a constantly changing
topographical map...

1319
02:03:32.471 --> 02:03:38.432
...flowing and shifting around the pole
in ripples 10,000 years wide.

1320
02:03:39.245 --> 02:03:40.735
So tell me...

1321
02:03:40.946 --> 02:03:45.349
...how would all of this be greatly improved
by an oil pipeline?

1322
02:03:45.785 --> 02:03:47.753
By a shopping mall?

1323
02:03:52.158 --> 02:03:56.458
So it's too much to ask for a miracle?

1324
02:03:56.595 --> 02:03:58.756
Miracles, by their definition,
are meaningless.

1325
02:03:58.898 --> 02:04:00.331
Oh, God, Jon!

1326
02:04:00.499 --> 02:04:05.596
- only what can happen does happen.
- Just stop your bullshit.

1327
02:04:06.639 --> 02:04:09.199
Land this thing. Now.

1328
02:04:09.341 --> 02:04:11.901
JoN:
As you wish.

1329
02:04:17.550 --> 02:04:18.608
You know what?

1330
02:04:18.818 --> 02:04:21.446
You can send me back to Earth
to fry with Dan and my mom...

1331
02:04:21.654 --> 02:04:24.020
...and all the other worthless humans.

1332
02:04:24.223 --> 02:04:27.624
But know that you were wrong.
You said this ended with me in tears...

1333
02:04:27.827 --> 02:04:31.957
...and look: nothing.
Maybe you were wrong about everything.

1334
02:04:32.131 --> 02:04:37.433
You complain that I refuse to see life
on life's terms...

1335
02:04:38.137 --> 02:04:41.937
...yet you continuously refuse
to see things from my perspective.

1336
02:04:42.074 --> 02:04:46.477
- You shut out what you're afraid of.
- l'm not afraid.

1337
02:04:46.645 --> 02:04:51.673
You want me to see things your way?
Go ahead, show me. Do that thing you do.

1338
02:04:58.858 --> 02:05:03.886
Magic. Dreams. That is what I had before.
l was a hero, goddamn it!

1339
02:05:04.096 --> 02:05:07.122
lt's not my fault you got old.
What do you have to complain about?

1340
02:05:07.299 --> 02:05:09.426
l put food on the table
for you and your child.

1341
02:05:09.602 --> 02:05:12.400
Call your friend Eddie.
Maybe he can give you a better life.

1342
02:05:13.138 --> 02:05:15.834
Even the grimy parts of it...

1343
02:05:16.208 --> 02:05:18.438
...keep on getting brighter.

1344
02:05:18.811 --> 02:05:20.608
You're Sally Jupiter's kid.

1345
02:05:21.514 --> 02:05:23.311
You're the Comedian, right?

1346
02:05:24.116 --> 02:05:25.811
You were pretty cool in there.

1347
02:05:26.218 --> 02:05:29.813
You know, your mom, she was one
of the all-time champion beauties.

1348
02:05:30.022 --> 02:05:34.425
- You got her eyes, you know. You got-
- Take your hands off her.

1349
02:05:34.627 --> 02:05:36.720
Hey, doll. Long time no see.

1350
02:05:36.929 --> 02:05:39.659
Not long enough in my book, Eddie.
Get in the car.

1351
02:05:40.165 --> 02:05:42.030
Now.

1352
02:05:43.035 --> 02:05:45.026
Are there no depths you won't sink to?

1353
02:05:45.170 --> 02:05:49.038
Jesus Christ, Sally.
Can't a guy talk to his...

1354
02:05:49.742 --> 02:05:51.437
...you know, old friend's daughter?

1355
02:05:53.746 --> 02:05:55.043
Drive.

1356
02:06:01.020 --> 02:06:03.818
lt was a mistake. One time.

1357
02:06:04.123 --> 02:06:07.286
Guy tries to rape you, and years later,
you let him finish the job?

1358
02:06:07.526 --> 02:06:10.222
What? Were you drunk or just lonely?

1359
02:06:10.396 --> 02:06:13.331
Am I ever gonna live this down?

1360
02:06:16.702 --> 02:06:17.828
Laurie.

1361
02:06:22.708 --> 02:06:24.039
No.

1362
02:06:26.045 --> 02:06:28.536
No, not him.

1363
02:06:28.747 --> 02:06:30.806
The Comedian...

1364
02:06:31.250 --> 02:06:33.309
...was your father.

1365
02:06:34.820 --> 02:06:36.515
No.

1366
02:06:39.825 --> 02:06:45.525
No! No! No!

1367
02:07:18.097 --> 02:07:20.088
My life is just...

1368
02:07:20.799 --> 02:07:22.892
...one big joke.

1369
02:07:23.102 --> 02:07:25.627
l don't think your life is a joke.

1370
02:07:27.306 --> 02:07:29.297
Yeah, well...

1371
02:07:31.110 --> 02:07:35.308
...l'm sorry if I don't
trust your sense of humor.

1372
02:07:43.522 --> 02:07:45.149
Will you smile...

1373
02:07:46.825 --> 02:07:49.316
...if I admit I was wrong?

1374
02:07:52.164 --> 02:07:54.155
About what?

1375
02:07:56.168 --> 02:07:57.658
Miracles.

1376
02:07:59.338 --> 02:08:02.466
Events with astronomical odds
of occurring...

1377
02:08:03.275 --> 02:08:05.766
...like oxygen turning into gold.

1378
02:08:05.978 --> 02:08:10.779
l've longed to witness such an event,
and yet I neglect...

1379
02:08:11.483 --> 02:08:13.883
...that in human coupling...

1380
02:08:14.687 --> 02:08:18.521
...millions upon millions of cells
compete to create life...

1381
02:08:18.991 --> 02:08:21.789
...for generation after generation...

1382
02:08:22.695 --> 02:08:25.721
...until finally, your mother...

1383
02:08:26.098 --> 02:08:27.292
...loves a man...

1384
02:08:27.933 --> 02:08:31.528
...Edward Blake, the Comedian,
a man she has every reason to hate...

1385
02:08:31.704 --> 02:08:35.697
...and out of that contradiction,
against unfathomable odds...

1386
02:08:36.408 --> 02:08:38.308
...it's you

1387
02:08:40.012 --> 02:08:41.343
only...

1388
02:08:42.047 --> 02:08:43.514
...you.

1389
02:08:44.416 --> 02:08:45.610
That emerged.

1390
02:08:46.218 --> 02:08:50.712
To distill so specific a form...

1391
02:08:50.923 --> 02:08:53.153
...from all that chaos...

1392
02:08:55.060 --> 02:08:58.029
...is like turning air into gold.

1393
02:09:02.367 --> 02:09:04.358
A miracle.

1394
02:09:07.873 --> 02:09:09.363
And so...

1395
02:09:09.875 --> 02:09:11.672
...l was wrong.

1396
02:09:13.679 --> 02:09:17.513
Now dry your eyes, and let's go home.

1397
02:09:45.110 --> 02:09:49.103
We got a bearing on that artificial structure.
Heat signature's off the charts.

1398
02:09:50.115 --> 02:09:53.209
- Veidt.
- I don't like the way Archie's kicking.

1399
02:10:01.627 --> 02:10:04.460
- The engines.
- They're icing up. Hold onto something.

1400
02:10:05.230 --> 02:10:07.255
Daniel, you're coming in too low.

1401
02:10:10.135 --> 02:10:13.332
Don't wish to interfere,
but perhaps should pull up sharply-

1402
02:10:13.472 --> 02:10:17.431
l know! l'm trying.
l'm trying to pull him up, goddamn it!

1403
02:10:44.703 --> 02:10:48.366
l'm gonna redirect the heat from
the flamethrower to speed up deicing...

1404
02:10:48.507 --> 02:10:51.374
...but it's gonna take a while
and we don't have time to wait.

1405
02:10:52.878 --> 02:10:54.368
You need something warmer.

1406
02:10:54.880 --> 02:10:57.075
Fine like this.

1407
02:11:26.545 --> 02:11:28.376
What is it, girl?

1408
02:11:30.749 --> 02:11:32.376
Mm.

1409
02:11:58.010 --> 02:12:00.240
Adrian's a pacifist.

1410
02:12:00.412 --> 02:12:05.042
He's a vegetarian, for chrissakes.
He's never killed anyone in his life.

1411
02:12:05.250 --> 02:12:06.649
Hitler was vegetarian.

1412
02:12:06.818 --> 02:12:11.312
You're squeamish, leave him to me.
We won't get second chance.

1413
02:13:22.627 --> 02:13:23.924
Gentlemen.

1414
02:13:24.429 --> 02:13:28.365
- Welcome.
- Adrian, we know everything.

1415
02:13:28.533 --> 02:13:30.330
Then what's there to discuss, Dan?

1416
02:13:30.469 --> 02:13:33.461
Plenty. You killed Comedian.

1417
02:13:33.638 --> 02:13:35.162
May he rest in peace.

1418
02:13:35.674 --> 02:13:38.268
Blake figured it out first.

1419
02:13:38.443 --> 02:13:42.539
Nixon had him keeping tabs on us,
making sure we weren't rocking the boat.

1420
02:13:43.482 --> 02:13:45.746
Blake found out what I was doing
here in Karnak...

1421
02:13:45.951 --> 02:13:49.944
...and by the time he visited poor Moloch,
he was cracking badly.

1422
02:13:50.155 --> 02:13:53.454
Even I couldn't predict he'd be the one
to have a change of heart.

1423
02:13:54.159 --> 02:13:55.683
So...

1424
02:13:56.762 --> 02:13:58.662
...l had to kill him.

1425
02:13:59.264 --> 02:14:02.927
Then I neutrali<i>z</i>ed Jon. No easy task.

1426
02:14:03.101 --> 02:14:05.592
l put roughly $2 billion
into tachyon research...

1427
02:14:05.737 --> 02:14:07.796
...to block Jon's vision of the future.

1428
02:14:07.939 --> 02:14:10.203
You used his psych profile
to manipulate him.

1429
02:14:10.709 --> 02:14:12.199
Got him to leave the planet.

1430
02:14:12.344 --> 02:14:15.745
l've known Jon long enough
to see he isn't devoid of emotion.

1431
02:14:15.947 --> 02:14:19.849
His subtle facial twitches wouldn't be
noticed by the layman, but to me...

1432
02:14:20.018 --> 02:14:21.849
...he might as well have been sobbing.

1433
02:14:22.220 --> 02:14:25.348
All I needed to do was tug on the thread.

1434
02:14:25.524 --> 02:14:27.424
The sudden flood of emotion Jon felt...

1435
02:14:27.626 --> 02:14:31.221
...when he came to believe
he'd given cancer to the people he loved...

1436
02:14:31.363 --> 02:14:33.524
...was all the excuse he needed
to leave Earth.

1437
02:14:33.665 --> 02:14:37.533
Your bullshit assassin.
You paid him to throw us off.

1438
02:14:37.669 --> 02:14:42.333
Mr. Chess gave his life
in the service of a higher cause, Dan.

1439
02:14:44.476 --> 02:14:47.570
l put a cyanide capsule in his mouth...

1440
02:14:47.746 --> 02:14:50.340
...leaving only one loose end:

1441
02:14:50.982 --> 02:14:54.440
You, and your mask-killer theory...

1442
02:14:54.586 --> 02:14:57.680
...one you followed
with the tenacity of a true sociopath.

1443
02:14:57.889 --> 02:14:59.584
l tipped off the police.

1444
02:14:59.758 --> 02:15:02.090
once you were in prison,
l was able to move forward.

1445
02:15:02.294 --> 02:15:04.888
Sorry to disappoint you.

1446
02:15:18.110 --> 02:15:20.544
We were supposed to make the world
a better place.

1447
02:15:20.712 --> 02:15:22.441
Dan, that's exactly what I am doing.

1448
02:15:22.647 --> 02:15:23.944
Nuclear war?

1449
02:15:24.149 --> 02:15:26.310
Human extinction?

1450
02:15:35.961 --> 02:15:40.864
of course, my moral safeguards
gave me pause at the necessary sacrifice.

1451
02:15:41.032 --> 02:15:44.024
A few key regions around the globe-

1452
02:15:44.169 --> 02:15:49.630
New York, Los Angeles, Moscow,
Hong Kong.

1453
02:15:49.841 --> 02:15:51.468
- disintegrated in an instant.

1454
02:15:52.244 --> 02:15:55.543
Fifteen million people killed...

1455
02:15:55.747 --> 02:15:57.772
...by Dr. Manhattan himself.

1456
02:15:59.050 --> 02:16:01.780
The world's punishment
for flirting with World War lll.

1457
02:16:01.920 --> 02:16:03.012
Jon wouldn't do that.

1458
02:16:03.622 --> 02:16:06.318
A fact no one outside this room
ever has to know.

1459
02:16:06.992 --> 02:16:10.792
The energy breakthrough I was working on
just came to fruition.

1460
02:16:11.396 --> 02:16:15.389
All these years, Jon was helping me
replicate his power...

1461
02:16:15.534 --> 02:16:18.094
...unaware of how I planned to use it.

1462
02:16:18.236 --> 02:16:20.227
You see...

1463
02:16:21.139 --> 02:16:23.539
...the Comedian was right.

1464
02:16:24.242 --> 02:16:29.236
Humanity's savage nature
will inevitably lead to global annihilation.

1465
02:16:29.447 --> 02:16:32.211
So in order to save this planet...

1466
02:16:32.517 --> 02:16:34.542
...l had to trick it...

1467
02:16:34.953 --> 02:16:38.946
...with the greatest practical joke
in human history.

1468
02:16:39.257 --> 02:16:42.658
- Killing millions.
- To save billions.

1469
02:16:43.228 --> 02:16:45.162
A necessary crime.

1470
02:16:45.330 --> 02:16:47.491
You know we can't let you do that.

1471
02:16:48.934 --> 02:16:51.061
"Do that," Rorschach?

1472
02:16:51.236 --> 02:16:52.863
l'm not a comic-book villain.

1473
02:16:53.738 --> 02:16:55.968
Do you think
l'd explain my masterstroke to you...

1474
02:16:56.141 --> 02:17:00.271
...if there were even the slightest possibility
you could affect the outcome?

1475
02:17:03.014 --> 02:17:05.778
l triggered it 35 minutes ago.

1476
02:18:45.317 --> 02:18:48.309
Jesus Christ, Henry.

1477
02:18:48.486 --> 02:18:50.716
Why the hell
didn't we get a launch detection?

1478
02:18:52.624 --> 02:18:57.027
lt's not the Soviets, sir.

1479
02:18:57.629 --> 02:19:00.689
lntel indicates the energy signature...

1480
02:19:00.865 --> 02:19:03.299
...was generated by...

1481
02:19:04.269 --> 02:19:06.703
...Dr. Manhattan.

1482
02:19:09.574 --> 02:19:11.098
Jon.

1483
02:19:14.112 --> 02:19:15.272
lnterference.

1484
02:19:15.880 --> 02:19:17.780
Cataclysmic interference.

1485
02:19:27.492 --> 02:19:30.290
l can't believe it happened.

1486
02:19:31.296 --> 02:19:34.788
This wasn't caused by nuclear warheads.

1487
02:19:38.837 --> 02:19:40.134
lt was me.

1488
02:19:42.207 --> 02:19:43.799
l...

1489
02:19:44.342 --> 02:19:45.400
...did this.

1490
02:19:46.010 --> 02:19:49.468
- What do you mean, you did this?
- Not directly.

1491
02:19:50.482 --> 02:19:53.144
lt was made to look like I did it.

1492
02:19:56.221 --> 02:19:57.654
Adrian.

1493
02:20:03.928 --> 02:20:05.919
Speak of the devil.

1494
02:20:09.067 --> 02:20:10.125
Jon-
l know.

1495
02:20:10.268 --> 02:20:12.429
Must stop him.
Killed Blake, killed millions.

1496
02:20:12.637 --> 02:20:13.934
Wait here.

1497
02:20:25.150 --> 02:20:27.482
Adrian, stop this.

1498
02:20:28.953 --> 02:20:30.853
The tachyons were clever...

1499
02:20:31.956 --> 02:20:36.290
...but even if I can't predict where you are,
l can turn the walls to glass.

1500
02:20:37.662 --> 02:20:40.096
l should thank you.

1501
02:20:41.266 --> 02:20:44.463
l'd almost forgotten the excitement
of not knowing...

1502
02:20:45.470 --> 02:20:48.462
...the delights of uncertainty.

1503
02:20:52.677 --> 02:20:54.304
Forgive me, girl.

1504
02:21:17.235 --> 02:21:18.930
You're such an asshole.

1505
02:21:52.904 --> 02:21:54.872
Veidt, you bastard.

1506
02:21:55.006 --> 02:21:57.474
- lf you've hurt her, l'll-
- Dan...

1507
02:21:59.210 --> 02:22:03.738
...grow up. My new world
demands less obvious heroism.

1508
02:22:03.948 --> 02:22:05.916
Your...

1509
02:22:06.117 --> 02:22:11.054
...schoolboy heroics are redundant.
What have they achieved?

1510
02:22:12.724 --> 02:22:15.557
Failing to prevent Earth's salvation...

1511
02:22:16.528 --> 02:22:18.928
...is your only triumph.

1512
02:22:19.130 --> 02:22:21.030
JoN:
l'm disappointed in you, Adrian.

1513
02:22:21.833 --> 02:22:25.325
l'm very disappointed.

1514
02:22:37.749 --> 02:22:40.877
Reassembling myself
was the first trick I learned.

1515
02:22:41.586 --> 02:22:43.986
lt didn't kill osterman.

1516
02:22:46.591 --> 02:22:48.957
Did you really think it would kill me?

1517
02:22:50.261 --> 02:22:53.458
l have walked across the surface
of the sun.

1518
02:22:53.965 --> 02:22:57.093
l have witnessed events
so tiny and so fast...

1519
02:22:57.268 --> 02:23:00.294
...they can hardly be said
to have occurred at all...

1520
02:23:00.438 --> 02:23:04.101
...but you, Adrian, you're just a man.

1521
02:23:05.209 --> 02:23:07.700
The world's smartest man...

1522
02:23:07.912 --> 02:23:10.437
...poses no more threat to me...

1523
02:23:10.648 --> 02:23:13.742
...than does its smartest termite.

1524
02:23:16.054 --> 02:23:17.521
What's that?

1525
02:23:17.922 --> 02:23:19.822
Another ultimate weapon?

1526
02:23:20.425 --> 02:23:22.154
Yes.

1527
02:23:23.761 --> 02:23:25.228
You could say that.

1528
02:23:28.766 --> 02:23:30.734
- came under attack.

1529
02:23:31.536 --> 02:23:34.869
Millions of lives were suddenly ended...

1530
02:23:35.239 --> 02:23:40.438
...in an act of evil
perpetrated by Dr. Manhattan himself.

1531
02:23:42.246 --> 02:23:46.182
Since the attacks,
l have been in constant contact...

1532
02:23:46.351 --> 02:23:49.343
...with the premier of the U.S.S.R.

1533
02:23:49.754 --> 02:23:52.587
Putting aside our past differences...

1534
02:23:52.957 --> 02:23:55.084
...we have both pledged to unite...

1535
02:23:55.460 --> 02:23:58.759
...against this common enemy.

1536
02:23:59.263 --> 02:24:01.197
With the rest of the world...

1537
02:24:01.633 --> 02:24:03.692
...we will prevail.

1538
02:24:06.204 --> 02:24:09.196
This is a day we shall never forget.

1539
02:24:09.407 --> 02:24:13.605
And yet we go forward
to defend the human race...

1540
02:24:13.745 --> 02:24:18.409
...and all that is good
and just in our world.

1541
02:24:19.751 --> 02:24:23.983
Thank you. God bless us all.

1542
02:24:24.355 --> 02:24:26.152
Do you see?

1543
02:24:28.359 --> 02:24:30.827
Two superpowers retreating from war.

1544
02:24:32.430 --> 02:24:34.864
l've saved the earth from hell.

1545
02:24:35.033 --> 02:24:37.001
We both have.

1546
02:24:37.468 --> 02:24:39.663
This is as much your victory as it is mine.

1547
02:24:44.475 --> 02:24:45.965
Now we can return...

1548
02:24:47.445 --> 02:24:48.969
...do what we were meant to.

1549
02:24:49.147 --> 02:24:52.139
We were meant to exact justice.

1550
02:24:52.483 --> 02:24:55.850
- Everyone's gonna know what you've done.
- Will they?

1551
02:24:55.987 --> 02:25:00.720
By exposing me, you would sacrifice
the peace so many died for today.

1552
02:25:00.892 --> 02:25:04.328
- Peace based on a lie.
- But peace...

1553
02:25:04.495 --> 02:25:06.690
- ... nonetheless.
- He's right.

1554
02:25:07.298 --> 02:25:11.234
Exposing Adrian would only doom the world
to nuclear destruction again.

1555
02:25:11.402 --> 02:25:14.303
No. We can't do this.

1556
02:25:14.439 --> 02:25:16.202
on Mars...

1557
02:25:17.709 --> 02:25:19.540
...you taught me the value of life.

1558
02:25:20.511 --> 02:25:22.945
lf we hope to preserve it here...

1559
02:25:23.815 --> 02:25:25.806
...we must remain silent.

1560
02:25:29.654 --> 02:25:31.622
Keep your own secrets.

1561
02:25:38.463 --> 02:25:39.657
Don't even think about it.

1562
02:25:42.266 --> 02:25:44.029
Rorschach.

1563
02:25:45.770 --> 02:25:47.328
Wait.

1564
02:25:48.339 --> 02:25:50.432
Never compromise.

1565
02:25:50.842 --> 02:25:53.675
Not even in the face of armageddon.

1566
02:25:54.078 --> 02:25:57.070
That's always been the difference
between us, Daniel.

1567
02:26:08.092 --> 02:26:11.619
l've made myself feel every death...

1568
02:26:13.097 --> 02:26:19.002
...see every innocent face
l've murdered to save humanity.

1569
02:26:24.609 --> 02:26:28.306
- You understand, don't you?
JoN: Without condoning...

1570
02:26:29.947 --> 02:26:31.847
...or condemning...

1571
02:26:36.320 --> 02:26:38.220
...l understand.

1572
02:26:45.630 --> 02:26:48.758
out of my way. People have to be told.

1573
02:26:49.634 --> 02:26:51.568
You know I can't let you do that.

1574
02:26:52.837 --> 02:26:55.829
Suddenly you discover humanity?

1575
02:26:57.241 --> 02:26:59.072
Convenient.

1576
02:27:07.785 --> 02:27:12.313
lf you'd cared from the start,
none of this would have happened.

1577
02:27:16.093 --> 02:27:19.085
l can change almost anything...

1578
02:27:23.634 --> 02:27:26.000
...but I can't change human nature.

1579
02:27:27.305 --> 02:27:30.706
of course
you must protect Veidt's new utopia.

1580
02:27:32.009 --> 02:27:35.308
What's one more body
amongst foundations?

1581
02:27:41.519 --> 02:27:43.419
Well, what are you waiting for?

1582
02:27:46.858 --> 02:27:48.723
Do it.

1583
02:27:54.832 --> 02:27:55.821
Do it!

1584
02:27:58.536 --> 02:28:01.869
No!

1585
02:28:19.390 --> 02:28:25.124
l'm leaving this galaxy
for one a little less complicated.

1586
02:28:25.296 --> 02:28:27.787
l thought you said you cared
about life again.

1587
02:28:27.999 --> 02:28:29.398
l do.

1588
02:28:30.701 --> 02:28:33.602
l think maybe l'll create some.

1589
02:28:37.708 --> 02:28:40.040
Goodbye, Laurie.

1590
02:29:15.279 --> 02:29:16.405
Come on.

1591
02:29:18.916 --> 02:29:20.474
Come on!

1592
02:29:24.922 --> 02:29:26.287
Dan...

1593
02:29:26.724 --> 02:29:29.488
...a world united and at peace.

1594
02:29:30.394 --> 02:29:31.588
There had to be sacrifice.

1595
02:29:31.729 --> 02:29:36.098
No! You haven't ideali<i>z</i>ed mankind,
you've deformed it.

1596
02:29:36.300 --> 02:29:38.029
You've mutilated it.

1597
02:29:38.402 --> 02:29:40.597
That's your legacy.

1598
02:29:49.113 --> 02:29:51.911
That's the real practical joke.

1599
02:30:44.568 --> 02:30:48.561
We repeat, there is
nothing wrong with your television set.

1600
02:30:48.773 --> 02:30:52.209
You are about to participate
in a great adventure.

1601
02:30:52.376 --> 02:30:55.573
You are about to experience
the awe and mystery...

1602
02:30:55.713 --> 02:31:01.515
...which reaches from the inner mind
to the outer limits.

1603
02:31:02.720 --> 02:31:04.915
Sure you don't want a drink?

1604
02:31:05.923 --> 02:31:06.912
l'm okay.

1605
02:31:08.025 --> 02:31:09.219
Cheers.

1606
02:31:10.661 --> 02:31:13.824
There's something I need
to get off my chest.

1607
02:31:15.066 --> 02:31:17.557
l know that Eddie Blake was my father.

1608
02:31:20.571 --> 02:31:22.334
Laurel.

1609
02:31:23.340 --> 02:31:25.672
What you must think of me.

1610
02:31:26.544 --> 02:31:29.035
l'm sorry I never told you.

1611
02:31:29.246 --> 02:31:31.043
l should have...

1612
02:31:31.248 --> 02:31:35.344
...but I don't know, I just felt ashamed.
l felt stupid.

1613
02:31:35.553 --> 02:31:37.453
lt doesn't matter.

1614
02:31:38.289 --> 02:31:43.556
People's lives take them strange places.
They do strange things...

1615
02:31:44.161 --> 02:31:47.062
...and, well,
sometimes they can't talk about them.

1616
02:31:47.264 --> 02:31:49.562
l know how that is...

1617
02:31:50.301 --> 02:31:52.895
...but I just want you to know...

1618
02:31:53.471 --> 02:31:56.304
...that you never did anything wrong
by me.

1619
02:32:00.411 --> 02:32:04.711
You asked me why I wasn't mad at him.

1620
02:32:06.317 --> 02:32:08.751
Because he gave me you.

1621
02:32:13.824 --> 02:32:14.916
Thanks, Mom.

1622
02:32:17.628 --> 02:32:19.425
l love you.

1623
02:32:26.971 --> 02:32:31.169
- Hello, Miss Jupiter.
- Oh, Sally, please.

1624
02:32:32.843 --> 02:32:37.439
Excuse me. Gotta go freshen up.
l'll be right back.

1625
02:32:47.958 --> 02:32:52.156
- So how's it going up here?
- Good. How's it going down there?

1626
02:32:52.296 --> 02:32:55.788
Good. I think l've got everything working.

1627
02:32:55.966 --> 02:33:00.528
All of Archie's systems are upgraded.
Finished the tinkering for now...

1628
02:33:00.704 --> 02:33:02.934
...so all we gotta do is take her out.

1629
02:33:03.107 --> 02:33:06.201
Well, that sounds like a date.

1630
02:33:17.521 --> 02:33:19.819
Are we gonna be all right?

1631
02:33:21.859 --> 02:33:26.159
Long as people think Jon's
still watching us, we'll be all right...

1632
02:33:26.363 --> 02:33:28.228
...in the end.

1633
02:33:29.867 --> 02:33:32.028
l know what Jon would say:

1634
02:33:32.236 --> 02:33:34.227
Nothing ends.

1635
02:33:36.140 --> 02:33:38.734
Nothing ever ends.

1636
02:34:26.123 --> 02:34:29.854
Seymour, we got nothing
to write about anymore.

1637
02:34:30.027 --> 02:34:31.426
Everyone in the country...

1638
02:34:31.562 --> 02:34:33.826
...every country in the world
are holding hands...

1639
02:34:34.031 --> 02:34:37.262
...and singing songs
about peace and love.

1640
02:34:37.768 --> 02:34:40.635
lt's like living in a goddamn
global hippie commune.

1641
02:34:40.838 --> 02:34:44.740
Well, Ronald Reagan says he's gonna
be running for president in '88.

1642
02:34:44.942 --> 02:34:46.739
We could run a piece on that.

1643
02:34:46.944 --> 02:34:50.072
Seymour, we don't dignify absurdities
with coverage.

1644
02:34:50.281 --> 02:34:54.149
This is still America, damn it.
Who wants a cowboy in the White House?

1645
02:34:54.852 --> 02:34:59.084
Okay. I could look for something
in the crank file.

1646
02:34:59.256 --> 02:35:00.780
Crank file.

1647
02:35:00.991 --> 02:35:02.982
Whatever. Take some initiative.

1648
02:35:03.127 --> 02:35:05.789
Run whatever you like.
l leave it entirely in your hands.

1649
02:35:12.303 --> 02:35:17.002
Rorschach's journal, October 12th, 1985.

1650
02:35:17.141 --> 02:35:21.601
Tonight, a comedian died in New York.